Queries

CatalogContent

Response

Returns a CatalogContent!

Arguments
Name Description
contentTypes - [String!]
labels - [String!]
layoutId - ID
page - Int!
query - String
resultsDisplayType - ContentItemDisplayType
sort - String
token - String
values - [String!]
widgetId - ID

Example

Query
query CatalogContent(
  $contentTypes: [String!],
  $labels: [String!],
  $layoutId: ID,
  $page: Int!,
  $query: String,
  $resultsDisplayType: ContentItemDisplayType,
  $sort: String,
  $token: String,
  $values: [String!],
  $widgetId: ID
) {
  CatalogContent(
    contentTypes: $contentTypes,
    labels: $labels,
    layoutId: $layoutId,
    page: $page,
    query: $query,
    resultsDisplayType: $resultsDisplayType,
    sort: $sort,
    token: $token,
    values: $values,
    widgetId: $widgetId
  ) {
    contentItems {
      ...ContentFragment
    }
    meta {
      ...CatalogMetaFragment
    }
  }
}
Variables
{
  "contentTypes": ["abc123"],
  "labels": ["abc123"],
  "layoutId": 4,
  "page": 123,
  "query": "abc123",
  "resultsDisplayType": "calendar",
  "sort": "xyz789",
  "token": "xyz789",
  "values": ["abc123"],
  "widgetId": 4
}
Response
{
  "data": {
    "CatalogContent": {
      "contentItems": [Content],
      "meta": CatalogMeta
    }
  }
}

CatalogQuery

Response

Returns a CatalogContent!

Arguments
Name Description
page - Int
query - String
queryExclusions - [String!]
queryLimit - Int
querySignature - String
querySort - String

Example

Query
query CatalogQuery(
  $page: Int,
  $query: String,
  $queryExclusions: [String!],
  $queryLimit: Int,
  $querySignature: String,
  $querySort: String
) {
  CatalogQuery(
    page: $page,
    query: $query,
    queryExclusions: $queryExclusions,
    queryLimit: $queryLimit,
    querySignature: $querySignature,
    querySort: $querySort
  ) {
    contentItems {
      ...ContentFragment
    }
    meta {
      ...CatalogMetaFragment
    }
  }
}
Variables
{
  "page": 987,
  "query": "xyz789",
  "queryExclusions": ["abc123"],
  "queryLimit": 987,
  "querySignature": "abc123",
  "querySort": "abc123"
}
Response
{
  "data": {
    "CatalogQuery": {
      "contentItems": [Content],
      "meta": CatalogMeta
    }
  }
}

Types

ID

Description

The ID scalar type represents a unique identifier, often used to refetch an object or as key for a cache. The ID type appears in a JSON response as a String; however, it is not intended to be human-readable. When expected as an input type, any string (such as "4") or integer (such as 4) input value will be accepted as an ID.

Example
4
